Dietician is responsible for assessing the nutritional care of the residents in the facility. He/she advises Administation and Food Service Director as needed all clinical aspects of the Food Service Department.





Responsibilities:


* Assess the nutritional status of residents includive of: lab value interpretation, consumption pattern, weight maintenance, food/drug interaction, dietary compliance;
* Performs assessment routine;
* Addressess appropriate nutritional concerns with all members of the nutrition support team;
* Give diet instruction for specific resident and families;
* Reviews resident care plans.


Requirement:


* Registered dietician with previous experience in a long term health setting or previous experience as a consulting dietician.
* Experience with geriatric population is preferred.
* Basic computer skills.
* Experience in menu writing with therapeutic extensions and extensive experience in patient assessment skills.
